      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb:3c297f1b2a",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "The interchange landscape"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "Utvekslingslandskapet"
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb:3c2b0f1ab3",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "2. Declare the content to localize"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "2. Oppgi innholdet som skal lokaliseres"
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb:3c31df8c5a",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "TM absorb on merge — every accepted target segment becomes a new\n  or updated translation unit (TU) in the project TM, carrying\n  provenance (merge batch id, source file path, block content hash,\n  originating XLIFF filename) so a later kapi tm audit --batch <id>\n  can trace every TU back to the merge that introduced it."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "**TM-absorbering ved fletting** — hvert akseptert målsegment blir en ny eller\n  oppdatert oversettelsesenhet (TU) i prosjektets oversettelsesminne, med\n  proveniens (flettebatch-id, kildefilsti, blokkens innholdshash, opprinnelig\n  XLIFF-filnavn) slik at en senere `kapi tm audit --batch <id>` kan spore hver TU\n  tilbake til flettingen som innførte den."
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb:3d3377a5ef",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "macOS (amd64, arm64)"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "macOS (amd64, arm64)"
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb:3e62075617",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": "The one thing to avoid: running two stateful stores over the same content —\nan ad-hoc .klz workspace and a .kapi project for the same files. Use the\n.klz workspace when there is no project; use the project store when there is."
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": "**Det ene du bør unngå:** å kjøre **to tilstandsfulle lagre over samme innhold** —\net ad hoc `.klz`-arbeidsområde *og* et `.kapi`-prosjekt for de samme filene. Bruk\n`.klz`-arbeidsområdet når det ikke finnes noe prosjekt; bruk prosjektlageret når\ndet gjør det."
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "docs-nb:3fcb20b72f",
      "hintSrcLang": "en",
      "variants": {
        "en": [
          {
            "text": ":::note\nkapi also speaks MCP, for assistants that prefer structured tools\nover a CLI. This page follows the skill (CLI) path — the two work together.\n:::"
          }
        ],
        "nb": [
          {
            "text": ":::note\nkapi snakker også [MCP](/reference/mcp), for assistenter som foretrekker\nstrukturerte verktøy fremfor en CLI. Denne siden følger ferdighetssporet (CLI) —\nde to virker sammen.\n:::"
          }
        ]
      },
      "created": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z",
      "updated": "2026-06-11T08:02:59Z"
    },
